LOGIN SCRIPT (PHP):

- Creating a "db_connect.php" file with the data needed to connect to the database. Implement it in the file "login.php".
- MySQL database connection "accounting app".
- Creation of session variables from data from the login form and from the database. 
- Assigning database data to session variables
- In the case of an incorrect LOGIN or PASSWORD, create a session variable "log_error_login" or "log_error_pass" and assign an error message to it. The message will be displayed in the login form in case of an incorrectly entered password. The session variable "log_error_login" will be deleted at the time of correct finding a user. The session variable "log_error_pass" will be deleted at the time of correct login.
- wyświetlanie komunikatu niepoprawnego hasła w przypadku, gdy podane hasło nie zgadza się z hasłem zapisyanym w bazie danych.

In the "loginform.php" file:
- opening of the session
- display of an invalid password message if the password is not entered correctly.
- storing the user's login in a session variable and then displaying it in the input in case of a failed login.

SQL injection security:
- htmlentities.
- mysqli_real_escape_string.

Also: 
- Change the linking in the home page navigation (index.php) from .html to php split.
- Remove unnecessary comments.
- Correction of error (typo) in "loginform.php" file from "methiod" to "method".
    
